e Technical and Development Committee to submit a shortlist of candidates for the positions of Head Coaches of the U-15 Boys National Team among other national teams. In the same vein, the federation has concluded plans to have a female fashion of the NFF/Zenith Bank U-15 after witnessing the success story of the male cadre. Apart from looking for a coach for the U-15 boys, the NFF has also mandated its Youth Football Committee to conclude the modalities for the staging of the first-ever U-15 Future Super Falcons’ Tournament, in the mode of the NFF/Zenith Bank U15 Super Eagles Championship that has been running for the past four years. Meanwhile, Zenith Bank has promised to continue to support football development, especially from the grassroots as they look forward to the return of the Future Eagles competition that was suspended due to the outbreak of the COVID-19 Pandemic across the world. Vanguard The Nigeria Football Federation and financial giants, Zenith Bank PLC, have expressed confidence that more future stars will emerge as the second edition of NFF/Zenith Bank U-13/U-15 Future Eagles Stars Championship takes centre stage. August 31, 2017 In "Sports" A new chapter was opened in Nigeria football on Monday when the Nigeria Football Federation and Zenith Bank PLC announced a partnership for youth football development and capacity building programs. September 15, 2015 In "Sports" The Managing Director and Chief Executive officer of Zenith Bank Plc, Peter Amangbo, has expressed delight over the recent partnership agreement with the Nigeria Football Federation on three key projects including grassroots development. September 18, 2015 In "Sports"